<chapter id="introduction">
<title>Introduction</title>

<para>
&multisynk; is a frontend for &kde;'s synchronization framework
kitchensync. This framework let you synchronize a lot of mobile devices
like handhelds and mobile phones with your KDE desktop, but also offers
the possibility to synchronize two or more KDE desktops directly.
</para>

<para>
The graphical user interface is similar to multisync, so everybody who have
ever worked with it should be familiar with multisynk as well.
</para>
</chapter>

<chapter id="using-multisynk">
<title>Using &multisynk;</title>

<sect1 id="general">
<title>General Information</title>

<para>&multisynk; is based on the kitchensync framework. The purpose of this framework is to
synchronize a couple of data records (events, todos, contacts), where the synchronization algorithm
knows nothing about the data. The actual synchronization is done between a so called konnector pair.
A konnector pair consists of two data providers (konnectors) which load the data from a source (a file,
a mobile device or the network), hand it over to the synchronization engine and write back the synchronized
data to the source.
</para>

<para>Additionally every konnector pair can give the synchronization engine hints how conflict resolution
shall be handled. Either it's done automatically (e.g. when a contact is changed on the PC and the handheld,
always overwrite the contact on the handheld) or manually, then a dialog will appear where the user can
choose which data record she wants to keep.
</para>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="getting-started">
<title>Getting Started</title>

<para>
After you have started &multisynk; (either using the panel menu or by typing
<command>multisynk</command> at the command prompt) the &multisynk; main window
will be displayed:

<screenshot>
<screeninfo>Starting &multisynk;</screeninfo>
<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="mainwin.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>The &multisynk; main window.</phrase></textobject>
<caption><para>The &multisynk; main window.</para></caption>
</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<para>
From the menubar or the toolbar you can execute the following commands:

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>New</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>Create new konnector pair.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Edit</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>Edit the selected konnector pair.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Delete</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>Delete the selected konnector pair.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Log</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>Show the dialog which displays the log information of current
synchronization process.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Sync</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>Synchronize the selected konnector pair.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</para>

<sect2 id="add-konnector-pair">
<title>Add Konnector Pair</title>

<para>
To add a new konnector pair just click on the first icon in the toolbar or select
New from the File menu.

The following dialog will appear:

<screenshot>
<screeninfo>New Konnector Pair Dialog</screeninfo>
<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="editdialog.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>The new konnector pair dialog.</phrase></textobject>
<caption><para>The new konnector pair dialog.</para></caption>
</mediaobject>
</screenshot>

In this dialog you can select the konnectors which shall be part of the konnector
pair, they can be configured by clicking on <guibutton>Configure...</guibutton> after selected the
<link linkend="konnectors-chapter-available">type</link>.
Additionally you can give the pair a name for better distinction in the konnector pair overview.
</para>

<para>On the second tab of the konnector pair edit dialog you can choose how conflict
resolution shall be handled.

<screenshot>
<screeninfo>New Konnector Pair Dialog</screeninfo>
<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="editdialog-conflicts.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>The new konnector pair dialog.</phrase></textobject>
<caption><para>The new konnector pair dialog.</para></caption>
</mediaobject>
</screenshot>

The following behaviours are possible:
<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Resolve it manually</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>A dialog will appear where you can choose which entry you want to keep.
</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Always use the entry from the first plugin</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>Always the entry from the first konnector is used.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Always use the entry from the second plugin</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>Always the entry from the second konnector is used.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><guilabel>Always put both entries on both sides</guilabel></term>
<listitem><para>The changed entries are duplicated on both sides.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</para>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="edit-konnector-pair">
<title>Edit Konnector Pair</title>
<para>
To change the settings of a konnector pair, just select it in the konnector pair overview
and choose <guilabel>Edit...</guilabel> from the toolbar or menubar. The appearing dialog
is the same like the one you get when adding a new konnector pair.
</para>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="delete-konnector-pair">
<title>Delete Konnector Pair</title>
<para>
To delete a konnector pair, just select it in the konnector pair overview
and choose <guilabel>Delete</guilabel> from the toolbar or menubar. An confirmation dialog
will show up and ask you whether you really want to remove the konnector pair.
</para>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="start-sync-process">
<title>Start Synchronization Process</title>
<para>
After you have <link linkend="add-konnector-pair">added</link>
a konnector pair, you can select it in the konnector pair overview and press the
<guilabel>Sync</guilabel> button in the toolbar or choose the action from the menubar.
The progress of the synchronization is shown by the status column in the konnector
pair overview and the <link linkend="log-dialog">log dialog</link>.
</para>
</sect2>

<sect2 id="log-dialog">
<title>The Log Dialog</title>
<para>
The log dialog collects all information of the synchronization progress and displays them
with a timestamp in a separated window.

<screenshot>
<screeninfo>The Log Dialog</screeninfo>
<mediaobject>
<imageobject><imagedata fileref="logdialog.png" format="PNG"/></imageobject>
<textobject><phrase>The log dialog.</phrase></textobject>
<caption><para>The log dialog.</para></caption>
</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>
</sect2>

</sect1>
